  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the ttukbaegi-earthenware-cook to 375F (190C).",
    "Arrange the Morbier cheese slices on the baking sheet, leaving space between each slice.",
    "Drizzle the olive oil over the cheese, then sprinkle the chopped parsley and chives on top.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Bake the cheese in the preheated oven for 10 minutes, or until lightly browned and melted.",
    "While the cheese is baking, toast the crusty bread until crispy.",
    "Assemble the ploughman's by placing a slice of toasted bread on a plate, topping it with a slice of baked Morbier cheese, a few pieces of smoked salmon, and a sprinkle of parsley and chives.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!",
    "Repeat with the remaining ingredients for additional servings.",
    "Garnish with lemon wedges and additional parsley, if desired.",
    "Serve with a side of chutney or mustard, if preferred."
